        "id": 283465,
        "name": "\ud83d\udc4a\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83d\udd25",
        "username": "Avitus",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-26T05:51:28.856Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Messages are queued on the server for 14 days before they\u2019re purged. Since they\u2019re not being delivered in the background, they were sitting on the server waiting to be delivered. Messages on Signal have to be delivered in order or it\u2019ll cause a decryption error and all the messages in the sequence will be lost from the decryption error onward. That\u2019s why you saw the messages get delivered when things were syncing. You can\u2019t find them now because they were, in fact, deleted.</p>",
