        "id": 283468,
        "name": "\ud83d\udc4a\ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8\ud83d\udd25",
        "username": "Avitus",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/{size}/34172_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-26T06:08:41.246Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That\u2019s correct, because you linked your phone to your PC to be able to use the Desktop app, and messages get sent to the smartphone and any linked device.</p>\n<p>The messages are encrypted on the sender\u2019s device, queued for delivery on the server, still encrypted, until the receiving device makes a connection to the service so they can be delivered. The content and metadata of the messages are never known to the server. Once that connection is made, the messages are purged from the server by being delivered, then decrypted, on the receiving device.</p>",
